MOST IMPORTANT C PROGRAMMING QUESTIONS
1
The most important questions repeated again and
again in the theory exam of C Programming: -
Q. 1 What is operating system? Explain main function of operating system and write
the name of operating system available in the market.
Q.2 Any number system conversion and doing basic operation like addition, subtraction,
division, multiplication on number system.
Q.3 Find the 2s complement and 1s complement?
Q.4 What is a Token in C Programming?
Q.5 Difference between Identifier and Literal?
or
Difference between variable and constant?
Q.6 Difference between While loop and do-while loop with syntax or example.
Q.7 Find the range and size of different data type in C Programming? And also write a format
specifier of data type?
Q.8 What is a pointer? Does the size of pointer depend on the variable or not?
Q.9 Difference between structure and Union?
Q. 10 What is the storage class? Define the different types of storage class with its scope
and life!
Q. 11 Difference between the Compiler, Interpreter and assembler?
Q.12 Difference between the Local variable and Global Variable?
MOST IMPORTANT C PROGRAMMING QUESTIONS
2
Q.13 What is an actual argument and Formal argument?
Q.14 What is the Reserve Word? How many reserve words in C language?
Q.15 What is the dynamic memory allocation? Difference between malloc( ), calloc( ),
realloc( ) and Free( ) function?
Q.16 Difference between RAM and ROM?
Q.17 Explain the difference between parameter passing procedure Call by Value and
Call by Reference/Address with example and write code also. Which is more efficient
and why?
Q.18 What is an algorithm? And What is the flow chart? Write an algorithm of any problem
and also draw a flow chart.
Q.19 Explain the string handling and file handling function in details?
Q.20 What is a Function? Explain why function prototype is essential.
Q.21 What is a recursion? Write a function to find the factorial of a number using recursion?
Q.22 Draw a basic block diagram of computer system? And explain each and every
part. Describe the working of computer system?
Q.23 Difference between hardware and software?
Q.24 What is an operator in C Language? And also explain the operator precedence and
associativity.
Q.25 What is a macro? Explain with example?
Q.26 Write a program of any problem without main function? And is it possible that to write
a program without main function and how?
Q.27 What is an Escape sequence?
Q.28 Describe the information security concepts and security threats.
Q.29 Difference between linear search and binary search?

Q.30 What is an array? Difference between Array and String? Write a program to find

That topic from which questions always come in the exam: -
[These given marks are as per the last six years papers and these topics are
expected.]
1. Number system (5-10 marks)
2. Write a C program or find out output and flow chart [From any topics] (30-60 marks)
3. Looping Statements, Array, String, Function, Pointer, Structure and Union, File
Handling (30-40 Marks)
4. Short Notes (10-20 marks)
